1
00:00:00,360 --> 00:00:05,950
Is it a good idea to display luxury brands and other signals of status

2
00:00:06,050 --> 00:00:08,140
It depends on the situation

3
00:00:08,580 --> 00:00:14,760
Studies have shown that people who appear to be wealthy tend to be considered more intelligent

4
00:00:14,820 --> 00:00:18,360
disciplinedand competent than those who do not

5
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:29,050
But new research found that people believe someone who shows off their social status cares more about benefiting themselves than helping others

6
00:00:29,340 --> 00:00:33,060
This means people are less willing to collaborate with them

7
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:37,660
Modesty may be key when cooperation is essential

8
00:00:37,840 --> 00:00:41,320
but the researchers also found that in some cases

9
00:00:41,340 --> 00:00:43,860
status signaling has advantages

10
00:00:44,540 --> 00:00:54,290
Experiments showed that participants were less likely to choose someone who signals their wealth or status to join a group seeking cooperative members

11
00:00:54,640 --> 00:01:00,910
but participants were more likely to choose that person when they were looking for a competitive member

12
00:01:01,590 --> 00:01:08,130
These findings suggest that people should change how they present themselves depending on their social goal

